This paper deals with text classification and augmentation techniques using deep learning models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of deep learning models, which falls under the category of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of Word2vec and WordNet, which are commonly used in information retrieval (IR) and artificial intelligence (AI) applications, respectively, making cs.IR and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of round-trip translation, which is a technique used in deep learning models, making cs.DL (Deep Learning) a possible sub-category.
